posts.author: Joe Anderton
posts.title: Black Eyed Peas' Fergie reveals she was "hallucinating on a daily basis" due to her addiction
posts.text:
Black Eyed Peas' Fergie Reveals She Was "Hallucinating on a Daily Basis" Due to Her Addiction 
She also thought the FBI were tracking her. Getty By Joe Anderton Dec 7, 2017 Black Eyed Peas and Poseidon star Fergie has spoken quite candidly about her crystal meth drug addiction before. And now she's speaking about the extent of how she was affected by the substances she was taking. "At my lowest point, I was [suffering from] chemically induced psychosis and dementia," she told i News . Advertisement - Continue Reading Below "I was hallucinating on a daily basis. It took a year after getting off that drug for the chemicals in my brain to settle so that I stopped seeing things. "I'd just be sitting there, seeing a random bee or bunny." At one point she tried finding sanctuary in a church, but explained that they tried to throw her out because she thought she was being tracked by an FBI infrared camera. "I remember thinking, 'If I walk outside, and the SWAT team's out there, I was right all along," she said. "But if they're not out there, then it's the drugs making me see things and I'm going to end up in an institution. And if it really is the drugs, I don't want to live my life like this any more, anyway'. "I walked out of the church; obviously there was no SWAT team, it was just me in a parking lot. It was a freeing moment. "The drugs thing, it was a hell of a lot of fun… until it wasn't. But you know what, I thank the day it happened to me. Because that's my strength, my faith, my hope for something better." This year has seen Fergie split from husband Josh Duhamel (but in this interview she says they are still close) and FINALLY release her second solo album Double Dutchess .

posts.title: Take a Sneak Peek at the New Emojis for 2018!
posts.text:
YOU ARE HERE: HOME > NEWS > TAKE A SNEAK PEEK AT THE NEW EMOJIS FOR 2018! Take a Sneak Peek at the New Emojis for 2018! 
This is just the beginning… Busang Senne 
Just when we were getting used to the emoji universe of new dinosaurs and expressive yellow smileys, the list of new emojis for 2018 has been released and it’s the emoji pack of our dreams. 
It’s only a matter of time before emojis replace words. Before you know it, we’ll have enough in the iOS lexicon to have entire conversations using only smiling turds and unicorns. Welcome to the future, folks. 
The first emoji was created in 1999 by a Japanese web developer, Shigetaka Kurita. But since Apple introduced emojis to iOS in 2011, they’ve become a pop-culture sensation. The colourful expressions and inanimate objects peppered in our everyday online conversations even have their own movie. Clearly, we’re obsessed. 
via GIPHY 
2018 emojis are giving much-needed representation for bald people, redheads and people with curly hair. Not to mention, they’ve finally included a sad poo emoji, llama, stick of dynamite, and all the other items you didn’t think you needed … until now. 
Don’t get your hopes up too high just yet, though – some emojis you have your eye on may change or even be rejected when it comes to deciding the final batch early next year. Even then, the new emojis will only be up, running and ready to use in the second half of 2018. Ugh! 
Still, they look really cute and at least there’s a sad poo to go with the happy one – it’s all about balance.

posts.author: Abs-Cbn News
posts.title: LOOK: Jessy stuns in bikini as she hits the beach with Luis | ABS-CBN News
posts.text:
She recently opened about how she learned to be at "peace" and "drown out the noise."
And Jessy Mendiola looks more confident and carefree as she showcased her stunning figure in a bikini while on her beach break in Boracay with boyfriend, Luis Manzano.
The actress shared her curvy snaps on Instagram, accompanying it with a hashtag telling herself to keep "fighting" as she turned 25.
 A post shared by Jessy Mendiola (@senorita_jessy) on Dec 6, 2017 at 3:52am PST
 A post shared by Jessy Mendiola (@senorita_jessy) on Dec 6, 2017 at 10:57pm PST
Mendiola was voted the "sexiest" woman in the country last year by reader's of FHM men's magazine. But the feat attracted more bad than good, resulting in numerous harsh, body-shaming comments.
In her birthday post, she reflected back on the past year Quote: : "I was so scared to be myself, to love without hesitation and to live my life the way I wanted to."
"Many times I would doubt myself, always listen to what other people would think or say, always try to please others, because that was me. I would sacrifice my own happiness for someone else’s pleasure, even if it meant getting hurt."
She then described herself as "very happy" at this point in her life, before adding: "I realized that happiness is something you work hard for. It’s something you decide to be everyday."
"Now that I’m a year wiser, I promise myself that there will be no holding back anymore. I will keep choosing happiness. To the people who stood by me through my highs and lows and have encouraged me to never give up, thank you. You know who you are, I will be forever grateful."

thread.title: ‘I jumped and closed my eyes’ – why a goal from a keeper has lit up Serie A
thread.title_full: ‘I jumped and closed my eyes’ – why a goal from a keeper has lit up Serie A

posts.author: highvelocitysportsnews
posts.title: ‘I jumped and closed my eyes’ – why a goal from a keeper has lit up Serie A
posts.text:
2-2 The Damned United 
In October, the mayor of Benevento Clemente Mastella expressed his regret that the city was becoming a byword for being terrible at something purely on account of the football club’s woeful results. 
The former Inter and Udinese manager, Andrea Stramaccioni now with Sparta Prague, upset a lot of Benevento fans when he told Czech journalists they should maybe think twice about overreacting to his team’s bad run. “It’s not like we’re Benevento,” he said. 
Your heart bled for them. Their fairytale story of back-to-back promotions was turning into a nightmare. 
Reaching Serie A for the first time ever was supposed to be a moment to savour. Not leave a sour taste in the mouth. Benevento won promotion to Serie A through the play-offs 
Benevento’s rise brought succour to a city, about an hour and a half’s drive west of Naples, that had suffered greatly when flooding caused €1.2bn worth of damage to the region in 2015. They were a symbol of hope and offered an escape from life’s problems for 90 minutes a week. 
Now they were a laughing stock. A punch-line. And clubs like Napoli used Benevento as a reason why Serie A needs to return to an 18-team format. Less quantity. More quality. 
Benevento’s owner Oreste Vigorito hit back, pointing out Benevento had actually out-spent Napoli and seven other teams in the summer. 
The trouble was it looked like a terrible waste of money, particularly when Benevento lost 6-0 at the San Paolo in September. 
Results like that did nothing to discourage the idea of Benevento being out of their depth. And when Marco Baroni got the sack a month later, the name of his replacement did not inspire great confidence. 
Roberto de Zerbi was a continuity appointment of sorts. His only top flight experience came at Palermo last season where he was fired after losing seven straight. Perfect for Benevento then, or so the joke went. 
In the meantime, captain Fabio Lucioni tested positive for the banned substance clostebol. He is appealing against the decision and hopes to be cleared. The substance in question was in a spray used to treat a graze. 
All it did was deepen the feeling Benevento were the Damned United. 
And yet it’s not like they have been out-played every week. Eight of their 14 defeats have been by one goal. 
And if Serie A hadn’t been experimenting with Video Assistant Referees, Benevento would have registered their first point back in August. Alberto Brignoli is on loan at Benevento from Juventus 
What made Brignoli’s equaliser all the more satisfying on Sunday is the number of times his team has lost in stoppage time themselves, often in comical circumstances. 
In October, Benevento drew level with Cagliari in injury time only to concede again with seconds to spare. 
Then three weeks ago their wait for a point again looked over when Sassuolo’s Domenico Berardi missed a penalty in added time. All Benevento had to do was see out one last corner. But even that was beyond them. 
Brignoli made a Taibi-like gaffe in that game. 
But De Zerbi retained faith in him and was rewarded on Sunday. On returning home that night, Brignoli received a hero’s welcome. There was a banner and a bottle of bubbly waiting for him outside his apartment. 
Sprayed in red paint was the message: “GRANDE ALBERTO!!! THANK YOU!!!” 
Reflecting on Brignoli’s goal, Taibi recalls how the one he scored for Reggina very nearly helped keep them up. 
“Even if we lost our next two games, from that moment our season changed. It created a positive atmosphere around the club and we fought for survival right until the end…” 
It didn’t stop Reggina being relegated in a play-off with Verona. “But those last two months were special,” Taibi said. 
For now, all Benevento have got is a point to their name. The number one. The same as a goalkeeper wears fittingly. 
They may be last but Brignoli’s goal is arguably one of the first things people will remember about this season in Serie A for years to come. 
Soccer News

posts.author: noreply@blogger.com (Aaren Jobs)
posts.title: Director Data Shopkick Redwood City
posts.text: Director Data Shopkick Redwood City   At Shopkick, the leading in-store shopping app in the USA, data is the life force that drives our entire business and the key ingredient needed for delivering personalized consumer experiences and meaningful insights to our Brand and Retail partners. We are looking for an inspirational Director of Data that not only excels in the science and mathematics of large data analysis and has demonstrated the art of managing a diverse team, but also loves composing and driving a data vision to bolster product and business initiatives.This role may be for you if ... You love the broad challenge of managing the strategic direction and tactical needs of a diverse set of data-related disciplines including Business Intelligence, Data Analytics, Data Science, Fraud, Machine Learning, Engineering … you know, the more the merrier! You love enabling people across the company to explore, learn, and adapt from the data around them. Ah heck, computers are basically just people with less personality, so let’s enable them too (and we’ll solve the personality part later!) Your day is not fulfilled until you know your teams’ efforts have put a smile on the face of someone in Sales, Marketing, Finance, or Product. You define your success by your team’s success and strive to make your teams as successful as possible. You value driven, supportive, collaborative co-workers who respect quality. In a typical week you might ... Work with Finance and Sales to improve revenue predictions and identify profit drivers Work with Marketing team to assess effectiveness of use acquisition campaigns by channel / LTV Work with Data Scientists and Engineers to develop content personalization models / algorithms Work with PMs, Data Analysts and Data Platform team to improve analysis and exploration tools Perform reviews of reports, models and code reviews of SQL Perform 1:1s with your team members and provide career guidance Mentor Data Analysts, Data Scientists and Engineers on methodologies, data quality, query design, data driven software development and clear communication of findings We are looking for ... 10+ years of experience solving sophisticated business and product problems using data 3+ years experience managing data analysts, data scientists and/or engineers with a data focus Expert knowledge of SQL and one of Python, Scala and/or Java Experience with big data systems / tools (e.g. Hadoop, Spark, Hive, Pig, MapReduce, Tableau) Strong working knowledge in the majority of the following data areas: data analytics, data mining, machine learning, personalization, and experiment design and analysis Excellent team player with strong communication skills (verbal and written) Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Statistics or Economics Extra points if you have ... PhD in Statistics Experience building and maintaining data platforms / products. Fluent in either R or Matlab. Experience with real-time data processing systems (e.g. Spark Streaming, Storm, Kafka, Flink) Familiarity with methods for detecting fraud Experience managing remote team members
